250 g Chorizo Sausage, uncased
½ cup Couscous
1 unit(s) Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
1 tbsp Moroccan Spice Blend
2 unit(s) Honey
113 g Mirepoix
28 g Almonds, sliced
56 g Baby Spinach
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
1 tbsp Chicken Stock Powder
0.13 tsp Pepper*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*

Once water is boiling, add 1 tsp (2 tsp) chicken stock powder and couscous. Remove from heat and stir to combine.
Cover and let stand, 5 min.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then chorizo and mirepoix. Cook, breaking up chorizo into smaller pieces, until no pink remains and veggies are tender-crisp, 3-4.

Add Moroccan Spice Blend, remaining chicken stock powder and garlic puree. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1-2 min
Add crushed tomatoes. Cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened slightly, 2-3 min.
Add honey and spinach. Cook, stirring occasionally, until spinach is wilted, 1-2 mins.
Season with salt and pepper.

When couscous is tender, fluff with a fork.
Stir 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter and almonds into the couscous.

Divide couscous between plates.
Top with chorizo tagine-inspired stew.
Sprinkle feta over top.